<section class="page-container section-spacer">

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 6rem); align-items: start;">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow fade-in">Story</p>
      <h2 class="fade-in-up delay-1">
        From one brain to many.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="fade-in-up delay-2">
      <p class="body-large" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        elly started as a personal tool. I have ADHD. Every productivity app I tried eventually made me feel worse, streak-shaming, feature bloat, subscription fatigue. So I built the thing I actually needed.
      </p>
      <p class="body-large" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        A notes app that doesn't judge. A calendar that makes time visible. An AI assistant that creates things instead of just chatting about them. A habits tracker where missing a day doesn't destroy weeks of progress.
      </p>
      <p class="body-large" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        It's self-hosted because your brain data shouldn't live on someone else's server. It's open source because you should be able to verify that claim. And it's encrypted because privacy isn't a feature, it's a prerequisite.
      </p>

    </div>
